1. Make sure the following are ready:
1. Ubuntu server running (AWS EC2)
2. Domain configured in DNS
3. Domain pointing to server public IP
4. Nginx installed
5. Backend application running on port 3000

Example domain: api.sahipata.com


2. Create Nginx Configuration
> cd /etc/nginx/sites-available/
> sudo vi sahipata-backend
  server {
    listen 80;
    server_name api.sahipata.com;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:3000;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;

        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;

        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
    }
}


3. Enable the Nginx Site
> sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/sahipata-backend /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/

4. Test Nginx Configuration
> sudo nginx -t

5. Restart Nginx
> sudo systemctl restart nginx



6. Install Certbot (Let's Encrypt Client)
> sudo apt install certbot python3-certbot-nginx -y

7. Generate SSL Certificate
> sudo certbot --nginx -d api.sahipata.com


8. Certbot Updates Nginx Configuration
Note - this will automatically update 


9. Verify HTTPS

10. Verify Certificate Auto Renewal
> sudo certbot renew --dry-run

If no errors appear, renewal is configured correctly.
